**Explanation**
The basic idea behind this question is to increment the number of cells traversed after every column and row operation. So if we can perform these two operations and increment the number of cells it needs to traverse next, we simply reach the solution. 
In this solution, I have checked if the number of steps required is odd or even. In case of odd, we need to increase the indices by 1 and decrease by 1 in case of even, i.e., go right or south in case of odd steps and west or north in case of even steps. 

**Hope this helps!**
