# EXPLANATION
We created 2-D vector **v** for our traversal.
Stored the given coordinates in **i** and **j** respectively.
Created a 2-D vector **ans** for our answer.

Let's see the idea:-
We took bool
a = for traversal left to right (if possible)
b = for traversal top to bottom (if possible)
c = for traversal right to left (if possible)
d = for traversal bottom to top (if possible)
The idea is to keep track of 4 index to check if traversal is possible or not. The coordinates of 4-index are stored in vector **p**.
In the first set of the conditions we we checked if the 4 point are going to lie in **v** or not.
Inside big while loop
We traversed in spiral form and on every inner loop, we checked if we are not out of vector and simultaneously added the coordinates in **ans**.
Finally returned the answer.
IT WILL BE BETTER IF THE CODE IS DRY RUN FOR JUST ONE SPIRAL MOVEMENT, FOR BETTER UNDERSTANDING.
In this we need to check for condition of corner cases too.
# SOLUTION
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> spiralMatrixIII(int rows, int cols, int rStart, int cStart) {
        vector<vector<int>> v(rows,vector<int>(cols,0));
        int i=rStart,j=cStart;
        vector<vector<int>> ans;
        bool a=true,b=true,c=true,d=true;
        vector<vector<int>> p={{i,j},{i,j+1},{i+1,j},{i,j-1}};
        if(p[1][1]>=cols)
            b=false;
        if(p[2][0]>=rows)
            c=false;
        else if(p[2][1]+1<cols)
            p[2][1]++;
        if(p[3][1]<0)
            d=false;
        else if(p[3][0]+1<rows)
            p[3][0]++;
        while(a || b || c || d){
            if(a){
                int x=p[0][0],y=p[0][1];
                while(y<cols && y!=p[1][1])
                    ans.push_back({x,y++});
                p[0][0]--;
                if(p[0][0]<0)
                    a=false;
                (p[0][1]-1<0)?:p[0][1]--;
            }
            if(b){
                int x=p[1][0],y=p[1][1];
                while(x<rows && x!=p[2][0])
                    ans.push_back({x++,y});
                p[1][1]++;
                if(p[1][1]>=cols)
                    b=false;
                (p[1][0]-1<0)?:p[1][0]--;
            }
            if(c){
                int x=p[2][0],y=p[2][1];
                while(y>=0 && y!=p[3][1])
                    ans.push_back({x,y--});
                p[2][0]++;
                if(p[2][0]>=rows)
                    c=false;
                (p[2][1]+1>=cols)?:p[2][1]++;
            }
            if(d){
                int x=p[3][0],y=p[3][1];
                while(x>=0 && x!=p[0][0])
                    ans.push_back({x--,y});
                p[3][1]--;
                if(p[3][1]<0)
                    d=false;
                (p[3][0]+1>=rows)?:p[3][0]++;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

