# Approach
###### Simulate the walk, ignoring whether we stay in the grid or not, and record positions of the grid in the order we encounter them.
###### Keep track of the count of steps needed in current direction. When it becomes zero, turn clockwise and reset the counter, incrementing it every second time.
###### Take the unit vector $$(0, 1)$$ pointing to the right as the start move direction. When it's time to turn, use the force of science to get a new heading. As the math says, the orthogonals to vector $$(A, B)$$ are vectors $$(-B, A)$$ and $$(B, -A)$$, the former is original turned $$90^0$$ counter-clockwise and the latter is $$(A, B)$$ turned $$90^0$$ clockwise, which is what we need.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(max(R, C)^2)$$. Potentially, our walk needs to spiral until we move $$R$$ in one direction, and $$C$$ in another direction, so as to reach every cell of the grid.
- Space complexity: $$O(R*C)$$, the space used by the answer.

# Code
```
class Solution
{
    struct Coord
    {
        var i, j: Int
        init(_ i: Int, _ j: Int) { self.i = i; self.j = j }
        static func += (lhs: inout Coord, rhs: Coord) { lhs.i += rhs.i; lhs.j += rhs.j }
    }

    func spiralMatrixIII(_ rows: Int, _ cols: Int, _ rStart: Int, _ cStart: Int) -> [[Int]]
    {
        var coord = Coord(rStart, cStart), direction = Coord(0, 1)
        func isInGrid() -> Bool {
            coord.i >= 0 && coord.i < rows && coord.j >= 0 && coord.j < cols
        }

        let cellCount = rows * cols
        var visited: [[Int]] = [], steps = 1, maxSteps = 2
        while true
        {
            if isInGrid() {
                visited.append([coord.i, coord.j])
                if visited.count == cellCount { break }
            }

            if steps == 0
            {   // turn clockwise
                (direction.i, direction.j) = (direction.j, -direction.i)
                // calculate amount of steps in new direction
                maxSteps += 1
                steps = maxSteps / 2
            }
            // advance in the current direction
            coord += direction
            steps -= 1
        }
        return visited
    }
}

```
