# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The simple approach that comes to mind is traverse in spiral direction from the current position, if we are within matrix are we will add that to our ans otherwise ignore, this way we will cover all indexes.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
start from current index and start traversing in spiral way,
Comments are added in code for more clarity.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
if size of matrix is X then max we will iterate 4*X indexes.
O(4*X)
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(X)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int[][] spiralMatrixIII(int rows, int cols, int rStart, int cStart) {
        //set the size of matrix -1 because we already visited one position
        int size = rows*cols-1;
        //shift is the number of steps in one direction, we can also say one side of rectangle
        int shift = 1;
        //when to increase shift, we will increase shift after completing two sides
        boolean increaseShift = false;
        //op stands for operation, operations means the direction of traversal
        int op = 1;
        //start and end point
        int x=rStart;
        int y=cStart;
        //array to store ans
        int[][] ans = new int[size+1][2];
        //index of ans array
        int idx=0;
        //count of steps in one particular direction
        int currentCount=0;
        //we add the current position
        ans[idx][0]=rStart;
        ans[idx][1]=cStart;
        idx++;
        while(size>0){
            if(op==1){
                y++;
            }else if(op==2){
                x++;
            }else if(op==3){
                y--;
            }else if(op==4){
                x--;
            }
            //increase the count in this direction
            currentCount++;
            //if position is within our range then add to ans
            if(inRange(rows,cols,x,y)){
                    ans[idx][0]=x;
                    ans[idx][1]=y;
                    idx++;
                    size--;
            }
            //if current count is equal to max steps then...
            if(currentCount==shift){
                currentCount=0; //reset
                op++;   //change direction
                op=op%4;
                if(op==0){
                    op=4;
                }
                if(!increaseShift){ //logic to increase shift
                    increaseShift=true;
                }else{
                    increaseShift=false;
                    shift++;
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
    boolean inRange(int rows, int cols, int x, int y){
        if(x<0 || x>=rows){
            return false;
        }
        if(y<0 || y>=cols){
            return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
}
