# Intuition
<Moving in spiral and filling the value in v[t++] if ro and co lie in boundary>

# Approach
<moving in a spiral ,.. with the help .of direction(d) and displacement(a)>

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<$$O(n^m)$$>

- Space complexity:
<$$O(n*m)$$>

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
vector<vector<int>> spiralMatrixIII(int row, int col, int ro, int co) {
    int n=row*col;
    vector<vector<int>>v(n);
    int a=1;
    int t=0;
    int d=1;
    int c;
    while(t<n){
        c=a;
        while(c--){ // moving right 
            if(-1<ro && ro<row && -1<co && co<col){v[t++]={ro,co};}
            co+=d;
        }
        c=a;
        while(c--){  /// moving downward
            if(-1<ro && ro<row && -1<co && co<col){v[t++]={ro,co};}
            ro+=d;
        }
        d*=(-1); /// and we will change the direction 
        a++; /// we will increase the distane we will now cover ..
    }
    return v;
}
};
